You are an expert in historical handwritten documents.

Extract the entities listed in the tool schema from the following text.
The text comes from two sources:
- MARGE: a marginal note summarizing the act (type, number, key names)
- TEXTE COMPLET: the full body of the official act

General conventions:
- Preserve the original spelling of names exactly as written; never abbreviate
